        "width": 100,
        "height": 10
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt from your Office of application for Pension No. 152744, and to return it herewith, with such information as is furnished by the files of this Office.",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 50,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 30
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "It appears from the Rolls on file in this Office, that Aaron Chambers was enrolled on the 19th day of Sept., 1864, at Owensboro, Ky., in Co. \"G\", 118th Regiment of U.S. Cold. Infty Volunteers, to serve three years, or during the war, and mustered into service as a Private on the 19th day of Sept., 1864, at Owensboro, Ky., in Co. \"G\", 118th Regiment of U.S. Cold. Infty Volunteers, to serve three years, or during the war. On the Muster October Roll of Co. \"G\" of that Regiment, dated Whites Ranche, Tx., Feb. 6th, 1866, he is reported \"Hired of disease in field Hospital Co. Nov. 6/64.\"",
      "bbox": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 80,
        "width": 100,
        "height": 60
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "I am, Sir, very respectfully,",
